tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Finished T67 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Decorated high school career at Medina Valley High School consisted of being named a four-time all-district selection (2007-10), two-time individual state champion, and three-time individual district champion...Named to All-Freshman Team Conference USA at University of Houston...Named to the 2011 Conference USA Championships All-Tournament Team...In 2013 named the All-Conference USA First Team...Named to the All-American Athletic Conference team in 2014, as well as the PING All-Central Region Team...Competed in every team-scoring event during his career.
tourBios.personal: Big Dallas Cowboys and San Antonio Spurs fan...Dream foursome would include his dad, Steve Stricker and Adam Lowe...Enjoys spending time with his dogs and girlfriend off the golf course...Golf superstitions include using a 1957 silver dollar that has to be marked heads up...Bucket list items include winning the Masters with his parents watching...Twitter name is @CurtisReedGolf.

tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Finished T15 at the Florida Qualifying Tournament after prevailing in an 8-for-4 playoff to earn exempt status through the first half of the season...Closed with rounds of 65-67-65 to earn his first career top-10 at the National Capital Open with a T10...Shared the opening-round lead with an 8-under 64 at The Wildfire Invitational eventually posting a T18...Recorded the lowest round of the Mackenzie Tour season with a 10-under 60 Sunday at the Freedom 55 Financial Championship, finishing T5.
tourBios.personal: Big Dallas Cowboys and San Antonio Spurs fan...Dream foursome would include his dad and Steve Stricker...Twitter account is @CurtisReedGolf...Has shot a 14-under 57 twice at his home course of Alsatian GC in Houston, Texas.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA T was T5th in 2015 at the Freedom 55 Financial Championship.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T14th in Scoring Average (Actual) on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA TOUR Canada.
